### Change 2 — Detection entry (after line 1644, inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template`)

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 - uses [INST]/[/INST] markers without [SYSTEM_PROMPT].
    // Ministral/Magistral Large 3 carries [SYSTEM_PROMPT], so absence of it here
    // is the correct distinguisher (as required), and this check is safe after that handler.
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos && src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v0.3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

**Why it's correct:** Ministral 3 requires `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` + `[TOOL_CALLS]` + `[ARGS]` — our check is mutually exclusive. All other handlers use entirely different sentinel tokens (`<|channel|>`, `>>>all`, `<|tool_calls_section_begin|>`, etc.), so there's no ambiguity.

